1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Taiwan is now super-aged.
More than 4.6 million people here are 65 or older.
That is one in five.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Among them, sarcopenia - the gradual loss of muscle and strength -
may affect roughly one in ten older adults, or more.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Falls are the number two cause of accidental injury death in this age group:
about 25 deaths per 100,000 each year.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Sarcopenia is linked to about 1.5 to 2 times higher fall risk.
That makes movement quality matter.

5
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:26,000
What helps is well established:
regular strength and balance training,
from sit-to-stand to balance holds and supported squats.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Taiwan has nearly 5,000 community care centers.
But one worker cannot watch every movement.
That is the gap GemmaFit is built to fill.
